,"body":"Tripple-Barrier extension suggestion:  \r\n\r\nAdd magnitude move barriers not determined by percentage moves, for example, a 10 cent move.\r\n\r\nSay you are interested in some spread between two or more instruments.  This spread can be positive, negative or even zero.  The percentage moves don't make sense here.\r\n\r\nA quick fix would be to convert your spread to the dollar value invested since inception, a la etf trick.  However, sometimes the absolute magnitude of the move is of interest.\r\n\r\nAnother practical example in the futures space would be something like a limits up/down filter for events.","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hudson-and-thames/mlfinlab/issues/451/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hudson-and-thames/mlfinlab/issues/451/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}